My love ran deep 

Here I stood next to my mirrored like windows,withs letter in my hands, sobbing knowing my love that I 
gave him was all for nothing. The day I first met him, he was a man weighted down by sadness and his past.
We eventually realsied our feelings for each other were more than just love, it was a passionate
affection. I don't regret the time that I spent with him. It made me feel alive at the time. But then he
sent this letter that I currently hold with hands covered in the tears of despair. I don't want this love
to end, I never did.

The letter:

"My love, my sign of devotion, God's blessing which was sent upon me.
I never wanted it to be like this, I never had a choice either. My 
custodians have arranged a marriage with another lady to increase
the reputation of my family. In a thousands lives that I could
live in I would choose you every single time over anyone. I hope
you find someone else better than me that could love you better than
I did. I'm declaring a end to our devoted love. I don't want to 
leave you but, I have to. Please forgive me"

How dare he think that I could find someone more charming and gentle than him.